🩺 Diabetes Prediction App

A simple and interactive web app that predicts whether a person is likely to have Diabetes based on medical attributes such as glucose level, BMI, blood pressure, and insulin — powered by a Support Vector Machine (SVM) model and deployed using Streamlit.

🚀 Demo

🔗 Live App: https://diabetes-prediction123.streamlit.app/

🧠 Project Overview

This project uses the PIMA Diabetes dataset to train a machine learning model that classifies whether a person is diabetic or not.
The app provides a user-friendly interface for real-time prediction.

🧩 Features

✅ Clean and responsive Streamlit interface
✅ Predicts diabetes likelihood based on user input
✅ Uses SVM model for accurate classification
✅ Data preprocessing with StandardScaler
✅ End-to-end pipeline — from model training to web deployment

⚙️ Tech Stack
Python
Streamlit
Scikit-learn
Pandas
NumPy

📊 Dataset

The model is trained on the PIMA Indians Diabetes Dataset
Available on Kaggle: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/uciml/pima-indians-diabetes-database
